Here's what I'm digging up;
pylibmc supports it in django: http://gc-taylor.com/blog/2011/08/16/tip-pointing-pylibmc-unix-domain-socket/

From looking at code, it isn't clear to me that the URL isn't simply a value passed in to the underlying library (pylibmc) from dogpile.cache and used in whatever way. We should experiment with using a domain socket instead.

Confirmed new console installs have memcached listening on a domain socket,...

{code}
[root@g-05-03 eucaconsole]# ps aux | grep memcached
eucacon+ 21317  0.0  0.0 317852  6228 ?        Ssl  Jul08   0:08 memcached -d -p -u eucaconsole -m 64 -c 1024 -P /var/run/eucaconsole/memcached.pid -s /var/run/eucaconsole/memcached.sock -a 0700
{code}

Now we need to verify the upgrade case mentioned by Dima.
